companies have a history of paying better renewal rates than others the rates for cdtype annuities remain the same for the term  tip  if you purchase an immediate annuity with a “life with cash refund or life with installment refund” the listed beneficiaries will receive  of the remaining dollars  annuities avoid probate so select the right beneficiary tip    rates that look too good to be true usually are make sure to check the companies rating before purchasing and look for stable highly rated companies you also want to diversify dont invest all of your savings with  company  tip  income annuities spia’s usually provide the highest contractually guaranteed payout of any type of annuity if you need “income now” spias also have no fees   looking for retirement income our free report shops  annuities and highlights the companies with the highest guaranteed returns our free report compares  annuities from americas two largest annuity databases tip  insurance agents usually get paid more the longer the money is locked up  many states have banned annuities with terms over  years  you should do the same  tip  you might have seen annuity ads where an annuity earned  with no risk these come from uncapped index annuities these returns are possible when market indexes go up considerably keep in mind these returns are not normal  tip   be careful of the fees on variable annuities  variable annuities have many different layers of fees get an itemized breakdown of all of the fees  if your variable annuity earns  gross and you pay  in fees you may be better off in fixed products tip  shop around dont buy any annuity until you compare the rates benefits and fees of all of the products available   rates vary considerably the top  year fixed annuity is now paying  more interest than the bottom in our database   tip   index annuities   does it have a cap   in plain english how is the gain calculated  if you are looking at index annuities with an income rider we can compare  products