ty  rate this post a fixed annuity pays the person a fixed income for a fixed period ie for example for the next ten years a lifetime annuity plan on the other hand provides a fixed income till the annuitant is alive both plans will have their own unique kind of conditions so read the agreement before signing can i withdraw more money from the account  rate this post unfortunately before the regular cycle of payments start you cannot withdraw any money but when the income starts and if you are in the need of money due to any emergency you can get in touch with your insurance company although this feature might not be available in all companies so before you sign any papers scrutinize the terms and conditions what is a deferred annuity income  rate this post if you are opting for a deferred annuity income you will pay the insurance company a certain premium and get the income after a specified amount of time has passed for example if you’re  years old and wish to have a fixed income by the age of  then a deferred annuity income can be a feasible choice for you are there any rules in terms of medical conditions  rate this post no there are no such norms pertaining to the medical condition of the person but they might ask you to specify medical details in the form sponsored listings symptoms of asthma personaledoctorcom  asthma triggers  treatment about diet and nutrition personaledoctorcom  important information on diet and nutrition cancer awareness personaledoctorcom  read frequently asked questions on cancer quick fitness tips personaledoctorcom  find useful information about fitness and health related questions find answers for queries on health insurance find answers on how to apply for a credit card online find answers on how to open a business checking account find answers on how to open savings and checking accounts find answers on ira investments ask a question ask questions get answers help others and connect with people who have similar interests ask now se